# Playground responsive layout

When editing **`field-demo/projects/playground/`** shell or global layout, keep this unless the user asks otherwise.

**Wide:** `html` / `body` / `app-root` fill height; **`body { overflow: hidden }`**. Two columns: preview **flex-grows**; controls **fixed width**. Each column **`overflow-y: auto`**, **`min-height: 0`**, **`overscroll-behavior: contain`**.

**Narrow (`max-width: 900px`):** Controls **fixed** off-screen, slide in; **`pointer-events: none`** when closed. **Top-right** menu toggles drawer; **`env(safe-area-inset-*)`** on notched devices. Close: backdrop, second menu tap, **Escape**, resize **above** breakpoint. Keep **`viewport-fit=cover`** in playground **`index.html`** when tuning safe areas. **Keep breakpoint in sync** in SCSS (`$playground-drawer-max`) and TS (`PLAYGROUND_DRAWER_BREAKPOINT_PX`).

**Theme:** Handled via `ThemeService` (signal-based, sets `data-theme` attribute). All playground colors use `--pg-*` CSS custom properties defined in `styles.scss`; no `.theme-light &` nesting in component SCSS.
